decks.notes: This deck focuses on using Eldrazi creatures to ramp up mana quickly and control the board with powerful spells like Kozilek's Command and Malevolent Rumble. The goal is to overwhelm the opponent with big creatures like Emrakul, the Promised End and Devourer of Destiny. The deck utilizes cards like Ugin's Labyrinth and Eldrazi Temple to accelerate mana production and cast expensive threats early in the game. Sowing Mycospawn and Writhing Chrysalis provide additional tokens and versatility in combat. Overall, the deck aims to control the game until it can deploy massive Eldrazi threats to secure victory.

This deck focuses on utilizing cards like Goryo's Vengeance and Ephemerate to quickly reanimate powerful creatures like Griselbrand and Atraxa. By using Atraxa's abilities to proliferate, along with other support cards like Priest of Fell Rites and Solitude, the deck aims to control the board while setting up a powerful reanimation combo. Thoughtseize and Force of Negation help disrupt opponent's strategies, while the deck has a mix of lands and spells to support the combo strategy. Overall, the deck aims to quickly reanimate threats and overwhelm the opponent.
